decision_conditions:
Condition : 12 - No development shall take place, including any works of demolition, until a Construction Management Plan has been submitted to, and approved in writing by, the local planning authority. The approved Plan shall be adhered to throughout the construction period. The Plan shall include:
i. a site plan;
ii. confirmation that a pre-start record of site conditions on the adjoining public highway will be undertaken with Hounslow Highways and a commitment to repair any damage caused;
iii. the hours of demolition and construction work;
iv. safeguarding measures that would be put in place to protect the adjoining building (Axis House);
v. provision for the parking of vehicles of site operatives and visitors;
vi. provisions for loading, unloading and storage of plant and materials within the site;
vii. details of access to the site for the duration of construction including phasing arrangements;
viii. means to control and manage access and egress of vehicles to and from the site including vehicle turning and waiting areas, use of pre-booking systems etc;
ix. the erection and maintenance of security hoarding including decorative displays and facilities for public viewing, where appropriate;
x. measures to prevent the spread of mud, dust, etc onto the public highway such as the provision of wheel washing facilities at the site exit and a commitment to sweep adjacent roads;
xi. measures to control the emission of dust and dirt during construction;
xiii. a scheme for recycling/disposing of waste resulting from demolition and construction works (to include basement level excavation);
xiv. appropriate vehicle routes to and from the site;
xv. measures to ensure the safety of all users of the public highway in the vicinity of the site, especially at the access, with particular reference to cyclists and pedestrians.
All work on site shall be carried out in accordance with the approved details.
